# MovEazy — ship after every change

Whenever you finish edits in this repository (`moveazy-git`):

1. Run `npm run build` and fix any failures before committing.
2. `git add` the relevant files, commit with a clear message, and `git push origin main`.
3. Deploy hosting: `npx firebase-tools@13 deploy --only hosting --non-interactive` (project is configured in `.firebaserc`).

Do **not** wait for the user to say “deploy” or “push” — do this as part of the same turn after changes are complete, unless the user explicitly asks to skip deploy or only work locally.
